      "Effective treatments for tobacco and nicotine dependence include both behavioral therapies and FDA-approved medications. Research shows that combining behavioral treatment with medication produces better outcomes than using either approach on its own.",
      "Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT) for smoking cessation helps people recognize the situations and triggers that prompt them to smoke. It teaches relapse-prevention skills, such as relaxation techniques, along with effective coping strategies for managing the urge to smoke.",
